Comex copper futures posted smallerthan expected gains early because of commission houseresistance beginning at 62.90 cents basis May, brokers said.    Commission house selling has been entering between 62.90and 63.10 cents because many speculators remain nervous afterrecent sharp declines, brokers said.    Locals were buyers in sympathy with firmer precious metalsand trade houses bought scale down, brokers said.    May delivery was up 0.05 cent at 62.70 cents a lb in a62.85 to 62.55 cents range. Reuter&#3;